title: A Popular History of Ireland: from the Earliest Period to the Emancipation of the Catholics, Book 04
creator: Thomas D'Arcy McGee
description: LibriVox recording of A Popular History of Ireland, Book 04, by Thomas D'Arcy McGee. Thomas D'Arcy McGee was an Irish refugee and a father of the Canadian confederation. His work on Irish history is comprehensive, encompassing twelve books; Book 4 begins with the first Norman invasion of the island and continues to the end of the 13th century. (Summary by Sibella Denton) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B audiobook of Complete Series
